&lt;p&gt;Zola is seeking a high-caliber &lt;strong&gt;Senior Accountant &lt;/strong&gt;to join our finance team. The ideal candidate thrives in a fast-paced environment, possesses a sharp technical eye for GAAP compliance, and is motivated by the opportunity to scale accounting operations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BACKGROUND&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of progressive accounting experience; a mix of public accounting and in-house experience strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certified Public Accountant (CPA) license (active or in-progress).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong foundational knowledge of U.S. GAAP and proficiency with ERP systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;“Builder” Mentality: Find ways to make a process or accounting area better, faster and more accurate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel skills required. Experience leveraging AI/automation tools a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills with the ability to explain accounting treatments to non-finance stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Obsessive attention to detail and highest level of integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Month-End Close: &lt;/strong&gt;Prepare and post journal entries for key accounting areas including those areas which involve management estimation. Full ownership of balance sheet accounts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Variance analysis:&lt;/strong&gt; Prepare substantiated variance analysis vs. budget and prior year. Translate accounting results into narratives that non-finance stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audit and Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt; Serve as a key point of contact for external auditors; prepare audit workpapers, manage request lists, and ensure a seamless year-end audit process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Process Enhancement:&lt;/strong&gt; Proactively identify &quot;bottlenecks&quot; in the accounting cycle and implement automation, AI tools or workflow improvements to increase efficiency. Draft and maintain comprehensive formal process documentation; assist in the design and implementation of internal controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with teams to ensure accounting workflows reflect the current state of the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The salary range for this role is $90,000 - $100,000. This full-time role will be hybrid at our office in NYC (Tuesdays &amp;amp; Thursdays).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT ZOLA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re Zola, the wedding company that will do anything for love. We&#39;re reinventing the wedding planning and registry experience to make the happiest moment in our couples&#39; lives even happier. From engagement to wedding and decorating your first home, Zola is there, combining compassionate customer service with modern tools and technology… all in the service of love.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We built our entire platform from the ground-up in 2013, and quickly became the fastest-growing wedding company in the country. Our team has deep experience creating award-winning online and mobile products that are helpful, intuitive, and simply magical. We&#39;re proud to have investor partners including Female Founders Fund, Comcast Ventures, Goldman Sachs, Canvas Ventures, Thrive Capital and Lightspeed Venture Partners, among others.&lt;/p&gt;
